Kerr, Appellant, v. West Shore R. Co., Respondent. (Supreme Court, General Term, Third Department. July 6, 1889.) Appeal from circuit court, Ulster county. Action by Charles Kerr against the West Shore Railroad Company to compel the defendant to restore stream and highway crossings. For opinion of special term, see 2 N. Y. Supp. 686.

Argued before Learned, P. J., and Landon and Ingalls, JJ.

William Lounsbery, for appellant. F. L. Westbrook, for respondent.

No opinion. Judgment affirmed, with costs, on opinion of court below.
